  "text": "(a) the effective Mordell conjecture -a conjectural extension of the Faltings-Mordell theorem which involves an effective bound on the height of rational points of the curve C over the number field K in the Faltings theorem in terms of data associated to C and K, (b) the Szpiro conjecture, see below, (c) the Masser-Oesterlé conjecture, a.k.a. the abc conjecture (whose statement over Q is well known [CITATION_1] , and which has an extension to arbitrary algebraic number fields, see Conj. 14.4.12 of [CITATION_2] ), (d) the Frey conjecture, see Conj. F.3.2(b) of [CITATION_3] , (e) the Vojta conjecture on hyperbolic curves, see below, (f) arithmetic Bogomolov-Miyaoka-Yau conjectures (there are several versions).",
